# Testing Conventions

## Layout

- Place tests in a package-level `tests/` directory, **not** beside source files in `src/`.
- Mirror the `src/` directory structure inside `tests/` (e.g. `src/lib/api/admin/` → `tests/lib/api/admin/`).

```
apps/api/
  src/routes/me.ts          →  tests/routes/me.test.ts
  src/schemas/common.ts     →  tests/schemas/common.test.ts
packages/auth/
  src/client.ts             →  tests/client.test.ts
```

## Naming

- Use the `.test.ts` suffix (or `.test.tsx` for React components).
- One test file per source module; name matches the module under test.

## Imports

- Import source under test via relative paths into `../src/` (adjust depth for nested dirs).

```typescript
// tests/routes/me.test.ts
import { meRoute } from '../../src/routes/me';
```

- Do not add path aliases from `tests/` to `src/`; keep imports explicit.

## Runners

| Package | Runner | Command | Coverage |
|---------|--------|---------|----------|
| `apps/api`, `packages/auth`, `packages/logger`, `packages/jx3api` | Bun | `bun test` | `bun run test:cov` |
| `apps/web` | Vitest | `vitest run` | `vitest run --coverage` |

Run all suites from repo root: `bun run test`. Coverage: `bun run test:cov`.

Coverage artifacts: `coverage/lcov.info` (Bun/Vitest) and `coverage/index.html` (Vitest HTML report in `apps/web`).

## Web coverage

- `apps/web` enforces >= 90% coverage via `vitest.config.ts` thresholds.
- Exclude bootstrap/wiring files in `coverage.exclude` (auth re-exports, query client, logger, router shell, shadcn UI, generated routes, thin API proxy handlers, route entry pages).
- `createServerFn` wrappers stay thin; extract request/session logic into testable helpers (see `resolveSession` in `get-session.ts`).

- `apps/api` enforces >= 90% coverage via `bunfig.toml`.
- Exclude bootstrap/wiring files with `coveragePathIgnorePatterns`; test files are skipped via `coverageSkipTestFiles`.

## Style

- Prefer unit tests for pure logic and Elysia `app.handle()` for HTTP behavior.
- Mock `src/lib/auth` with `mock.module` when tests need a fake session or handler.
- Keep `src/` free of test-only helpers; shared fixtures belong in `tests/fixtures/` when needed.
- Route module tests can `.use(meRoute)` directly; register `mock.module` before importing the route.
